The paper proposes a Q-learning algorithm to optimize the bidding strategy for mobile app install ads in real-time bidding (RTB) environments. This involves managing multiple campaigns while maintaining efficiency, budget utilization, and profit. The paper also uses a state space to capture the current state of the system. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which falls under cs.IR (information retrieval) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems, which is a topic covered under cs.MA (multi-agent systems).
